text: And Buckley wrote the forward in Allard's book, barnesandnoble.com/p/never-s…

When I was growing up things were different. I babysat for my Congressman Allard Lowenstein's kids on L.I. One of Al's closest friend was William Buckley. How different they were - Al the most radical Democratic Congressman (perhaps in history) and Buckley, perhaps the leading
conservative in the US Watch the respect.... piped.video/watch?v=65qp5TTX…

I freakin' love this tweet.

If I learned some things after four decades investing is to be respectful of those with different views, be critical of smugness/hubris (Mr. Market is out to get all of us), be rigorous in analysis, say "I dont know" when "I dont know,"

not to feign answers to every question under the sun (esp those outside my competence), to admit my mistakes (they are many/frequent!), recognize that the invt mosaic is complex (avoid single factors like "unusual" activity ), not to use leverage, be diversified by co, and along

industry lines. To confidently say the" S&P will rise by +10% by year end" (given the plethora or uncertainties) or predict over $20k on bitcoin (its $6400 now) by Dec 31 based on positioning or any other variable is unwise, uncool and silly. coindesk.com/price/
